    "description": "made by four students in 2023-2024. Isocraft Story is a Minecraft-like sandbox game made of blocks and many dimensions/levels, taking inspiration from Subnautica, Minecraft and other crafting-related games.<br />\r\nPlace and break blocks, fight enemies, play with friends online, worldwide or in your local network. Shape the infinite and procedurally-generated blocks world of Isocraft Story. Collect materials, advance to higher tiers of tools and weapons, craft everything you like out of anything you find, go deeper into the world and build a new spaceship to escape from this planet...<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe player plays an intrepid galaxy explorer who has crashed on<br />\r\nthis strange planet. He is now responsible for rebuilding his ship, all<br />\r\nby trying to unravel the secrets of this extraterrestrial environment, through<br />\r\ncareful exploration and use of available resources.<br />\r\nBut the player is also encouraged to stay on this planet, to build<br />\r\nwhat he wants, from the small house in sandy earth to advanced civilization<br />\r\nthanks to the resources that he can find and assemble to progress with his<br />\r\nfriends in multiplayer.<br />\r\nAn essential concept of the game is the formation of the planet in &quot;layers&quot;<br />\r\nparallel and placed on top of each other, made up of cards from the game unique to<br />\r\neach part and sheltering unique fauna and flora. These layers serve as<br />\r\nprogression to the player, who ventures ever deeper into this universe<br />\r\nhostile, looking for its history, materials for its ship, and above all<br />\r\nadventure.",
